OL,6,FEach episode has "dropped" on the
OL,7,FiPlayer at 9pm on Sundays ` creating
OL,8,Fthe same sense of excitement and
OL,9,Fexpectation as waiting for a show on a
OL,10,Flinear channel.
OL,12,FIncredibly, the rise in overnight
OL,13,Fratings appears to suggest that some
OL,14,Fwho were catching up on the earlier
OL,15,Fepisodes on the iPlayer now switch on
OL,16,Fto BBC One at 9pm on Sundays.
OL,18,FThis is how it should be for a quality
OL,19,FBBC programme. The sense of expectation
OL,20,Fand the collective shared viewing
OL,21,Fexperience are all there.
OL,3,CStriking a balance between linear TV
OL,4,Cand streaming
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/9
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
